Why this is a problem
Using formatted strings in SQL queries can allow attackers to inject malicious SQL code if the variables are not properly sanitized, leading to potential data breaches or data loss.

How to fix it
Use prepared statements with parameterized queries, such as using 'SqlCommand' and 'SqlParameter' in C#, to safely include variables in SQL statements and prevent SQL injection.
